WEBVTT

1
00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:44.273
<i>[Man Narrating]
Let me tell you about my day so far.</i>

2
00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:46.271
<i>Coffee in Paris,
surfed the Maldives...</i>

3
00:00:46.360 --> 00:00:48.795
<i>took a little nap
on Mount Kilimanjaro.</i>

4
00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:51.793
<i>Oh, yeah, and I got digits
from this Polish chick in Rio.</i>

5
00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:53.791
<i>And then I jumped back...</i>

6
00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:56.554
<i>for the final quarter of the N.B.A. finals...
courtside, of course.</i>

7
00:00:56.640 --> 00:00:58.551
<i>And all that was before lunch.</i>

8
00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:00.551
<i>I could go on,
but all I'm saying is...</i>

9
00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:02.631
<i>I'm standing on top of the world.</i>

10
00:01:06.080 --> 00:01:07.991
The lighter terrain here...

11
00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:10.833
<i>[Man Narrating]
It wasn't always like this.</i>

12
00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:14.993
<i>Once I was a normal person,
a chump just like you.</i>

13
00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:20.189
- Hey, Millie.
- Oh, hey, David.

14
00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:25.877
You got a lot of cities there.

15
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:28.918
<i>Well, if you're gonna have a dream,
might as well dream big, right?</i>

16
00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:30.911
<i>- Right.
- [Bell Ringing]</i>

17
00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:32.957
See you later.

18
00:01:41.720 --> 00:01:44.633
Hey, Millie.

19
00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:48.670
Give me a sec.
Hey.

20
00:01:52.120 --> 00:01:55.750
I wanted to give you this.
I picked it up at a yard sale in Plymouth.

21
00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:57.831
I-I thought you'd really like it.

22
00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:06.191
It's a little dinged up
and it's missing a few steps, but...

23
00:02:07.880 --> 00:02:10.110
I love it.

24
00:02:10.200 --> 00:02:12.760
- You do?
- I do.

25
00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:14.399
<i>[Boy]
Holy crap, Rice Bowl!</i>

26
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:17.313
- Mark.
- Hey, what's this?

27
00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:19.311
- Christmas come early?
- Mark, stop it.

28
00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:21.550
- Mark, give it back to her.
<i>- Holy crap!</i>

29
00:02:21.640 --> 00:02:24.632
Look what David got Millie!
You guys like the Eiffel Tower?

30
00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:28.395
Wow, if you shake this thing hard enough,
you can hear the Eiffel Tower move.

31
00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:31.791
- Hey, who wants to give it a shake?
- Okay, that's enough!

32
00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:34.275
- Stop it. Just give it back.
- All right.

33
00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:36.351
Okay, I'm sorry.
Here.

34
00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:42.791
<i>[Students Laughing,
Chattering]</i>

35
00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:46.111
Sorry, buddy.
Guess I don't know my own strength.

36
00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:51.237
- I can't believe you're such a jerk!
- I was just playing around.

37
00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:54.438
<i>- It wasn't funny</i>
- [Chuckles] They thought it was pretty funny.

38
00:02:54.520 --> 00:02:57.558
<i>[Millie]
David?</i>

39
00:02:57.640 --> 00:03:00.359
David, don't go out there.
It's not safe.

40
00:03:00.440 --> 00:03:02.351
David, just forget about it.

41
00:03:02.440 --> 00:03:04.795
Come on, Rice Bowl!
Don't be stupid!

42
00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:08.271
David, come back. Come on.
Just let it go. It's okay!

43
00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:12.751
<i>Stop! It's not worth it.
Just come back. Please?</i>

44
00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:17.636
Come on, David!

45
00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:21.031
<i>[Millie]
Be careful Come on.</i>

46
00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:23.475
- All good. See?
<i>- [Mark] Great. Now come back.</i>

47
00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:26.392
<i>[Millie Screams]</i>

48
00:03:26.480 --> 00:03:29.359
- David!
- Millie, don't go out there!

49
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:33.877
<i>[Millie, Muffled]
David! David! Somebody...</i>

50
00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:37.396
- [Groaning, Muffled]
<i>- [Millie] Oh, my God!</i>

51
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:40.552
- David... Get help!
- Millie, get back here!

52
00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:43.553
<i>[Millie]
Please help! David!</i>

53
00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:46.393
<i>- Call9I I! David!</i>
- You can't help him!

54
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:48.232
<i>- Millie, stop, stop, stop!
- David!</i>

55
00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:50.072
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

56
00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:52.310
[Groaning]

57
00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.710
[Spitting, Coughing]

58
00:04:02.080 --> 00:04:04.549
<i>[Coughing Continues]</i>

59
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:14.552
<i>[David Narrating]
And that's how it happened the first time.</i>

60
00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:19.316
<i>One second I'm a goner, and the next thing
I know I'm at the Ann Arbor Public Library.</i>

61
00:04:32.680 --> 00:04:34.876
<i>Home, sweet home.</i>

62
00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:39.590
<i>Mom left when I was five.</i>

63
00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:43.719
<i>As for Dad, well, let's just say
he wasn't much of one.</i>

64
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.071
<i>You're late.
Supper's cold</i>

65
00:04:51.160 --> 00:04:54.596
[Men On TV,
Indistinct]

66
00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:57.320
<i>Where you been, anyway?</i>

67
00:04:57.440 --> 00:04:59.477
[Squishing, Squeaking]

68
00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:02.473
You know, when I ask a question,
I expect an answer. Okay?

69
00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:04.710
Hey, hey, hey.
What happened to you?

70
00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:08.791
Just kids at school.

71
00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:13.636
Hey, David, get back down here,
get a mop and clean this crap up!

72
00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:15.631
<i>David!</i>

73
00:05:15.720 --> 00:05:17.791
<i>Don't make me come up there!</i>

74
00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:20.434
<i>David?
Make the right choice!</i>

75
00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.638
<i>- [Door Rattling]</i>
- David! David.

76
00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:25.831
Open the door.

77
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:50.912
Did I just teleport?

78
00:05:53.800 --> 00:05:55.791
Great.

79
00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.355
I teleported to the library.

80
00:06:26.320 --> 00:06:29.233
<i>[Men Conversing,
Indistinct]</i>

81
00:06:29.320 --> 00:06:33.678
<i>Look... No, no, no. I'm not going anywhere.
I don't care what you say.</i>

82
00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:36.479
<i>[David Narrating]
And that's when it occurred to me.</i>

83
00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:40.076
<i>This thing that just happened,
it could set me free.</i>

84
00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:51.952
<i>And if she could run away
so could I.</i>

85
00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:57.911
You're okay.

86
00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:08.151
<i>[Tap On Window]</i>

87
00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:11.796
<i>[Tap On Window]</i>

88
00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:20.756
[Chain Squeaking]

89
00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.074
<i>[Squeaking Continues]</i>

90
00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:38.311
[Gasps]

91
00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:44.311
<i>[David Narrating]
I wanted to tell her everything.</i>

92
00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:46.431
David?

93
00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:49.751
David?

94
00:07:49.840 --> 00:07:52.480
<i>[David Narrating]
I mean, who would have believed me anyway?</i>

95
00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:54.517
<i>[Millie]
David!</i>

96
00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:57.592
<i>[David Narrating]
I figured it was time to move on.</i>

97
00:08:23.760 --> 00:08:25.717
U h, I'd like a room.

98
00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:29.156
You're not gonna be any trouble,
are you? No weird stuff?

99
00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:32.949
Nope.
No weird stuff.

100
00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:42.274
<i>[Dog Barking, Growling]</i>

101
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:47.991
[Chuckles]

102
00:08:51.960 --> 00:08:53.871
<i>[David Narrating]
And so there I was.</i>

103
00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:57.669
<i>I had a million questions,
like how does this thing work?</i>

104
00:08:57.760 --> 00:08:59.751
<i>How do I control it?</i>

105
00:09:14.960 --> 00:09:16.951
[Groans]

106
00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:48.911
Been there.

107
00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:51.958
<i>[David] Mommy, you can see
the ocean and everything!</i>

108
00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:54.634
If we're lucky,
maybe we'll see King Kong.

109
00:09:54.720 --> 00:09:56.631
- Really?
- [Laughs]

110
00:09:56.720 --> 00:10:00.190
- You got me?
- Oh, I got you. I'm not letting you go.

111
00:10:05.520 --> 00:10:08.319
<i>[Rumbling]</i>

112
00:10:24.920 --> 00:10:27.196
<i>[David Narrating]
I was 15.</i>

113
00:10:27.280 --> 00:10:30.830
<i>Come on.
What would</i> you <i>have done?</i>

114
00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:33.912
<i>I figured I'd pay it back someday</i>

115
00:10:39.880 --> 00:10:41.871
Is there a bathroom for customers?

116
00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:56.190
Hey.
It's this way.

117
00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:58.271
Yeah.

118
00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:01.351
Make it quick.

119
00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:03.636
No problem.
Thanks.

120
00:11:46.440 --> 00:11:48.556
I'm gonna need a bigger bag.

121
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:54.112
<i>♪♪ [Rock]</i>

122
00:11:54.200 --> 00:11:58.910
♪ <i>Hey, I'm not all alone</i> ♪

123
00:12:01.520 --> 00:12:06.037
♪ <i>Hey you can tag along</i> ♪

124
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:09.515
♪ <i>'Cause I have
done it before</i> ♪

125
00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:11.511
♪ <i>And I can do it some more</i> ♪

126
00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:13.352
♪ <i>I got my eye on the score</i> ♪

127
00:12:13.440 --> 00:12:16.114
♪ <i>I'm gonna crash through the door
It's too late♪♪</i>

128
00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:18.191
Holy shit.

129
00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:20.271
Whoo!

130
00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:23.391
<i>♪♪ [Rock Continues]</i>

131
00:12:23.480 --> 00:12:25.391
- Hey!
<i>- ♪♪ [Continues]</i>

132
00:12:25.480 --> 00:12:29.951
I said no weird stuff.
Let's go... two days' rent. You owe me rent.

133
00:12:30.040 --> 00:12:31.951
<i>- [Knocks]</i>
- Hello? Hello?

134
00:12:32.040 --> 00:12:34.031
<i>[Paper Slides]</i>

135
00:12:49.840 --> 00:12:52.753
The police and the F.B.I.
have already been through here.

136
00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:55.434
- Who are you with?
- N.S.A.

137
00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:57.955
<i>They couldn't make
heads or tails of it.</i>

138
00:12:58.040 --> 00:13:01.431
The vault has a time lock,
pressure mounts, steel plates.

139
00:13:01.520 --> 00:13:03.431
- This guy didn't open a door.
- Open a door?

140
00:13:03.520 --> 00:13:06.433
We didn't know we were robbed
until halfway through the day.

141
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:08.909
I want the security tapes
for the whole month.

142
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:12.914
And I need the name of everyone who has
a safety deposit box in that vault.

143
00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:15.992
That's confidential.
Why do you need those names?

144
00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:19.516
Whoever robbed your vault
has been in it before.

145
00:13:19.600 --> 00:13:22.672
Now, I want those names,
and I want those tapes.

146
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:24.717
Today.

147
00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:44.153
<i>[David Narrating]
So the story had a happy ending.</i>

148
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.949
<i>Rice Bowl was dead,
but I had never been more alive.</i>

149
00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:51.431
<i>So now I'm living in New York.</i>

150
00:13:51.520 --> 00:13:53.955
<i>[Chuckles]
But why settle in one place...</i>

151
00:13:54.040 --> 00:13:56.350
<i>when you can have the whole world?</i>

152
00:13:58.360 --> 00:14:00.829
♪ <i>I was hip to the beat
on city streets</i> ♪

153
00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:05.756
♪ <i>I saw a signpost tellin' me to pick my feet
off the ground, y'all</i> ♪

154
00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:10.633
♪ <i>Said "I think"
to the shrink</i> ♪

155
00:14:10.720 --> 00:14:13.280
♪ <i>I tell her
well, 'bout my lover</i> ♪

156
00:14:13.360 --> 00:14:16.716
♪ <i>She tell me, "Get a dog
that says bow-wow-wow"</i> ♪

157
00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:22.070
[Announcer]
She floats into the river.

158
00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:25.676
But as you can see, this flood became
more severe about 10 minutes ago.

159
00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:28.918
The question now, Pat, is,
what will happen to these people?

160
00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:31.116
<i>It would take a miracle
to get to them.</i>

161
00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:34.955
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

162
00:14:55.240 --> 00:14:57.231
<i>♪♪ [Fades]</i>

163
00:14:57.320 --> 00:14:59.470
<i>Good afternoon, Mr. Jones.</i>

164
00:15:01.040 --> 00:15:03.270
- How they doin'?
- Down by six at the half.

165
00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:06.273
Don't think you'll be
needing that umbrella.

166
00:15:06.360 --> 00:15:08.636
You never know.

167
00:15:08.840 --> 00:15:11.673
<i>[Bells Tolling]</i>

168
00:15:11.760 --> 00:15:13.751
<i>[Whoosh]</i>

169
00:15:15.320 --> 00:15:18.312
[Tolling Continues]

170
00:15:21.880 --> 00:15:24.713
<i>[Rain Pattering]</i>

171
00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:29.792
<i>[Bell Chiming]</i>

172
00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:32.872
<i>- ♪♪ [Rock]</i>
- [People Chattering]

173
00:15:52.800 --> 00:15:55.713
<i>- [Man] Watch it!
- [David] You mind if I join you?</i>

174
00:15:55.800 --> 00:15:58.440
<i>- [Woman] No.</i>
- What are you drinking?

175
00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:00.278
Gin and tonic.

176
00:16:00.360 --> 00:16:04.718
U h, Tanqueray and tonic.
Two of 'em, please.

177
00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:11.594
So, you live in London?

178
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:13.671
♪ <i>We lay down the law</i> ♪

179
00:16:13.760 --> 00:16:16.320
- Taxi!
<i>- ♪ So what the hell are you here for</i> ♪

180
00:16:16.400 --> 00:16:18.596
♪ <i>We lay down the law</i> ♪

181
00:16:18.680 --> 00:16:21.194
♪ <i>So what you need me for♪♪</i>

182
00:16:40.680 --> 00:16:42.159
[Whispers]
Shit.

183
00:16:53.720 --> 00:16:55.711
Dude, this totally sucks.

184
00:16:57.320 --> 00:17:00.233
Hey, I thought this was where the storm
was supposed to hit.

185
00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:03.039
- I heard it hit Fiji.
- Fiji, huh?

186
00:17:03.120 --> 00:17:05.839
Yeah. They got,
like, 30-foot swells.

187
00:17:05.960 --> 00:17:07.633
Really?

188
00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:16.231
Wh... Whoa!

189
00:17:16.320 --> 00:17:18.880
[Yelling]

190
00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:56.759
<i>- [Explosions, Gunfire]
- [Men Shouting]</i>

191
00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:03.758
<i>- [Groaning]
- [Explosions, Gunfire Continue]</i>

192
00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:10.830
Let's go.

193
00:18:13.360 --> 00:18:16.000
<i>- [Electricity Crackling]
- [Groaning Continues]</i>

194
00:18:17.600 --> 00:18:21.150
<i>¿Porqué?
¿Porqué?</i> Why?

195
00:18:21.240 --> 00:18:24.915
Because you are an abomination.

196
00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:27.953
<i>- [Electricity Crackling]</i>
- [Man Groaning, Screaming]

197
00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:31.158
Only God should have the power...

198
00:18:31.240 --> 00:18:34.039
to be all places at all times.

199
00:18:37.440 --> 00:18:40.432
[Grunts]

200
00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:50.556
[Whimpering]

201
00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:57.354
One less of you to worry about.

202
00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:02.396
Cut him down!

203
00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:05.154
Let's get the hell out of here.

204
00:19:05.240 --> 00:19:07.436
