- Yeah?

205
00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:10.433
We have a lead on the bank, sir.

206
00:19:10.520 --> 00:19:13.080
I'll be on the next plane.

207
00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:21.831
Hey, Angelo.
How'd they do?

208
00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:23.831
- Not so good.
- Ah.

209
00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:27.914
- Told you you wouldn't be needing that umbrella.
- Yeah. You were right.

210
00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:41.913
♪♪ [Whistling]

211
00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:43.991
♪♪ [Stops]

212
00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:48.076
<i>Don't run.</i>

213
00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:54.518
Eight years
we've been looking for you.

214
00:19:56.960 --> 00:19:59.759
And who are you?

215
00:19:59.840 --> 00:20:01.831
My name's Roland.

216
00:20:03.200 --> 00:20:06.272
- What are you doing in my apartment?
- Oh, we'll get to that.

217
00:20:10.600 --> 00:20:12.910
What kind of crook...

218
00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:14.991
leaves a note?

219
00:20:17.920 --> 00:20:20.833
- I think I need to talk to my lawyers.
<i>- Why?</i>

220
00:20:20.920 --> 00:20:22.672
You're not under arrest.

221
00:20:22.760 --> 00:20:25.832
- You mean you're not the...
- Police? Mm-mmm.

222
00:20:25.920 --> 00:20:27.831
Anybody can rob a bank.

223
00:20:27.920 --> 00:20:31.436
What I'd like to know is how you rob a bank
without opening any doors.

224
00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:33.431
<i>Come on.</i>

225
00:20:33.520 --> 00:20:36.433
<i>I'm sure you can think of something.</i>

226
00:20:36.520 --> 00:20:39.433
Look, uh,
if you're not the police...

227
00:20:39.520 --> 00:20:43.275
and I'm not under arrest...

228
00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:46.910
I think I'd like you to leave.

229
00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:53.956
- [Knob Rattling]
