<i>- Come on.</i>
- What?

471
00:36:57.600 --> 00:36:59.637
Come on.
How about a private tour?

472
00:36:59.720 --> 00:37:02.792
It's closed. We can't
break into the Colosseum.

473
00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:06.396
Who said it's closed?
The door was open.

474
00:37:06.480 --> 00:37:08.471
Wanna see the Colosseum or not?

475
00:37:10.680 --> 00:37:12.671
Come on.

476
00:37:12.760 --> 00:37:15.274
We so should not be doing this.

477
00:37:39.760 --> 00:37:41.751
<i>[Millie]
This place is amazing.</i>

478
00:37:41.840 --> 00:37:43.831
<i>[David]
I wanted you to see this.</i>

479
00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:46.753
You've gotta admit,
it's worth the risk.

480
00:37:47.760 --> 00:37:49.751
Yeah.

481
00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:58.194
- [Laughing] It's so cool!
- It is.

482
00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:08.316
Down here is where they used to keep
the gladiators and the lions in cages?

483
00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:11.995
- We should go down there.
- Can't go down there. It's off-limits.

484
00:38:12.080 --> 00:38:14.720
- Even when it's open.
- Nothing's off-limits.

485
00:38:14.800 --> 00:38:16.598
What?

486
00:38:16.680 --> 00:38:18.432
- [Scoffs]
<i>- [Whoosh]</i>

487
00:38:21.360 --> 00:38:23.078
Psst! Millie!

488
00:38:26.320 --> 00:38:28.994
Did that door just open too?

489
00:38:29.080 --> 00:38:31.037
- It's open now.
- Yeah.

490
00:38:31.160 --> 00:38:34.915
You're gonna want to see this.
Trust me.

491
00:38:41.160 --> 00:38:43.151
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

492
00:38:49.600 --> 00:38:51.637
<i>Bet you that's worth something.</i>

493
00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:54.030
<i>[Laughs]
Maybe.</i>

494
00:39:00.240 --> 00:39:03.870
[Chuckles]
Uh-oh.

495
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:06.110
I think he's telling you
do not enter.

496
00:39:07.680 --> 00:39:10.354
You speak Italian?

497
00:39:10.440 --> 00:39:12.351
No.

498
00:39:12.440 --> 00:39:14.351
- Well, uh, <i>l'ingresso...</i>
- Uh-huh?

499
00:39:14.440 --> 00:39:16.351
Means "come on in."

500
00:39:16.440 --> 00:39:19.671
Oh! I thought it meant "bullshit."

501
00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:22.673
Well, no, that means that you should
stay here while I go around...

502
00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:25.195
and open it from the other side.

503
00:39:25.280 --> 00:39:27.191
It's all right.
You'll catch on.

504
00:39:27.280 --> 00:39:29.271
Mmm.

505
00:39:32.800 --> 00:39:34.791
[Giggles]

506
00:39:40.840 --> 00:39:44.470
Thank you very much.
Next showing will be at 6:00.

507
00:39:44.560 --> 00:39:47.632
Don't forget to tip your usher.

508
00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:51.390
<i>- Oh, uh...</i>
- U h, do you mind, man?

509
00:39:51.480 --> 00:39:54.040
- Whoa!
- Just a little privacy, eh?

510
00:39:54.160 --> 00:39:55.719
- Sorry, man.
<i>- Big Colosseum. Guy peein'?</i>

511
00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:59.316
This isn't a fashion show.
I'm taking a piss. Do you mind?

512
00:40:01.000 --> 00:40:03.150
Place is all yours.

513
00:40:05.240 --> 00:40:07.151
[Shouts]

514
00:40:07.240 --> 00:40:11.438
Wouldn't open that door if I were you,
not if I wanted my girlfriend to keep breathing.

515
00:40:11.520 --> 00:40:15.115
<i>What are you gonna do anyway?
Bring her down, have a nice, romantic picnic?</i>

516
00:40:15.200 --> 00:40:18.113
Nice little tea party?
Is that what you think is gonna happen?

517
00:40:18.200 --> 00:40:20.999
- If you so much as look at her wrong...
- You gonna jump me? Where?

518
00:40:23.320 --> 00:40:26.358
Did you think you were the only one?

519
00:40:27.840 --> 00:40:29.911
You really have no idea, do you?

520
00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:31.911
You lead the life you live.

521
00:40:32.000 --> 00:40:34.833
<i>You think you can just go on a little
Roman holiday and they wouldn't notice?</i>

522
00:40:34.920 --> 00:40:36.831
Just jump
all over the place...

523
00:40:36.920 --> 00:40:38.831
jump, jump, jump,
jump, jump, jump...

524
00:40:38.920 --> 00:40:40.911
and nothing's gonna happen?

525
00:40:42.280 --> 00:40:44.669
Well, they've noticed.

526
00:40:44.760 --> 00:40:46.433
Not me.

527
00:40:46.520 --> 00:40:49.194
I mean I already knew.
I'm not talking about me, but them.

528
00:40:49.280 --> 00:40:51.271
Down there.

529
00:40:54.600 --> 00:40:56.637
Hello, boys.

530
00:41:00.040 --> 00:41:01.997
Just me, then.

531
00:41:02.080 --> 00:41:05.596
- [High-pitched Charging]
- Huh. That's new.

532
00:41:08.040 --> 00:41:11.476
[Grunting, Groaning]

533
00:41:17.760 --> 00:41:19.751
Welcome to the war.

534
00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:36.915
Just let me know if you guys
are gettin' tired.

535
00:41:38.400 --> 00:41:40.914
- Close.
- David?

536
00:41:43.400 --> 00:41:45.869
- [Screams]
- What's going on?

537
00:41:45.960 --> 00:41:48.156
[Panting]

538
00:41:50.600 --> 00:41:52.716
Great. Let's meet
the girlfriend, shall we?

539
00:41:52.800 --> 00:41:54.916
No.

540
00:42:06.440 --> 00:42:09.876
- [Grunts]
- Who are these people?

541
00:42:09.960 --> 00:42:11.871
Paladins.
Paladins kill Jumpers.

542
00:42:11.960 --> 00:42:13.792
I kill Paladins.
Class dismissed.

543
00:42:15.600 --> 00:42:19.195
<i>[Woman Speaking Italian]</i>

544
00:42:19.280 --> 00:42:21.749
<i>Polizia! Polizia!</i>

545
00:42:21.840 --> 00:42:23.558
<i>- Polizia!</i>
- Uh-oh.

546
00:42:25.280 --> 00:42:27.112
Wait!

547
00:42:34.200 --> 00:42:36.350
I just came through your jump scar.

548
00:42:36.440 --> 00:42:39.353
What do you think
you're doing here? Huh?

549
00:42:39.440 --> 00:42:41.829
If I were you, I'd jump right back.

550
00:42:41.920 --> 00:42:44.673
You're not supposed to see
all this stuff. Get out!

551
00:42:46.680 --> 00:42:51.436
So if you'd like to
kindly fuck off, as in now.

552
00:42:51.520 --> 00:42:53.989
Maybe your girlfriend's still alive.

553
00:42:54.080 --> 00:42:56.071
[Gasps]

554
00:42:57.160 --> 00:42:58.912
- Hey.
- Hey.

555
00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:02.594
- What happened to you?
- Uh, nothing.

556
00:43:02.680 --> 00:43:05.798
Let's go. Come on.
I think we should just get out of here.

557
00:43:05.880 --> 00:43:08.110
<i>[Millie]
That didn't sound like nothing.</i>

558
00:43:08.200 --> 00:43:11.955
You were right. Okay? I shouldn't have
gone down there. Everything's fine.

559
00:43:12.040 --> 00:43:15.078
Come on. We can
still make the museum.

560
00:43:16.160 --> 00:43:19.073
<i>[Sirens Wailing]</i>

561
00:43:20.560 --> 00:43:22.471
<i>- [Woman Speaking Italian]
- David?</i>

562
00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:24.471
<i>Will you talk to me?
Please?</i>

563
00:43:24.560 --> 00:43:26.471
Must be a cab around here somewhere.

564
00:43:26.560 --> 00:43:28.995
Why aren't you talking to me?
Please talk to me.

565
00:43:29.080 --> 00:43:32.471
- I'll tell you everything back at the hotel. Okay?
- I'm not waiting for the hotel.

566
00:43:32.560 --> 00:43:35.837
- Look, Millie, it's, uh... it's all fine. Okay?
- No, it's not all fine.

567
00:43:35.920 --> 00:43:39.197
- I wasn't supposed to go back there.
<i>- [Men Shouting In Italian]</i>

568
00:43:39.280 --> 00:43:42.477
- [Speaking Italian]
- H uh?

569
00:43:42.560 --> 00:43:44.471
Uh, <i>no comprende.</i>

570
00:43:44.600 --> 00:43:47.353
- [Italian]
- No, I think you guys made a mistake.

571
00:43:47.440 --> 00:43:50.000
- Be quiet.
- You're looking for that guy over there.

572
00:43:50.080 --> 00:43:54.278
- [Italian]
- I'm sorry. I know I wasn't
supposed to be back there.

573
00:43:54.400 --> 00:43:56.311
<i>[All Shouting]</i>

574
00:43:56.400 --> 00:43:58.516
<i>Calma, calma, calma, calma.</i>

575
00:43:58.600 --> 00:44:01.274
Can't you just let us off with a warning...
Whoa! Okay, okay.

576
00:44:01.360 --> 00:44:03.590
- [Italian]
- Okay, okay, okay.

577
00:44:03.680 --> 00:44:06.798
- Millie, just go back to the hotel. Okay?
- No...

578
00:44:06.880 --> 00:44:09.838
<i>- No, no, we're not together.</i>
- I'm with him!

579
00:44:09.920 --> 00:44:12.275
I don't know her.
Millie, go back to the hotel.

580
00:44:12.360 --> 00:44:15.751
- No. No.
- [Siren Wailing]

581
00:44:17.440 --> 00:44:20.671
I told you.
I want to see Millie.

582
00:44:20.800 --> 00:44:24.077
- Where is the body?
- I didn't do anything, okay?

583
00:44:24.160 --> 00:44:27.232
I-I don't know how many times
you want me to tell you the same thing.

584
00:44:31.320 --> 00:44:33.550
Do you know how much longer
he's gonna be back there?

585
00:44:33.640 --> 00:44:35.631
We wait for <i>magistrato.</i>

586
00:44:35.720 --> 00:44:38.758
Yeah. I know. We've been waiting for
a <i>magistrato</i> all night.

587
00:44:40.400 --> 00:44:43.119
[Speaking Italian]

588
00:44:43.240 --> 00:44:45.470
I don't speak your...
I don't know what you're saying.

589
00:44:45.560 --> 00:44:47.631
Now you "seat," or we seat you.

590
00:44:47.720 --> 00:44:49.711
- Okay.
- Seat!

591
00:44:49.800 --> 00:44:51.996
I seat.

592
00:44:52.080 --> 00:44:54.196
<i>- [David] She's got nothing to do with this.</i>
- [Speaking Italian]

593
00:44:54.280 --> 00:44:56.191
<i>[Italian]</i>

594
00:44:56.280 --> 00:44:58.191
[Italian]

595
00:44:58.280 --> 00:45:02.433
<i>Allora,</i> the magistrate is here.
We will hold on to your passport.

596
00:45:02.520 --> 00:45:05.672
<i>Don't worry
You won't need it where you're going.</i>

597
00:45:06.760 --> 00:45:09.149
<i>[Chattering In Italian]</i>

598
00:45:17.880 --> 00:45:19.951
Hello, David.

599
00:45:20.040 --> 00:45:23.556
<i>You've only got about 30 seconds before
they come through that door You understand?</i>

600
00:45:23.640 --> 00:45:25.597
You have to get out of here.

601
00:45:25.680 --> 00:45:28.433
- Ditch the girl. If she's with you, she's dead.
<i>- Mom.</i>

602
00:45:28.520 --> 00:45:31.478
- Mom.
- Twenty seconds, David.

603
00:45:33.000 --> 00:45:36.914
Mom! Mom!

604
00:45:37.000 --> 00:45:38.035
Hey!

605
00:45:38.120 --> 00:45:40.839
[Grunts]

606
00:45:40.920 --> 00:45:43.480
<i>- [Handcuffs Click]</i>
- [Whimpers]

607
00:45:51.840 --> 00:45:53.319
Millie.

608
00:45:54.640 --> 00:45:57.359
All done. You okay?

609
00:45:57.480 --> 00:45:59.437
Mm-hmm. Hey.

610
00:45:59.520 --> 00:46:02.353
- I'm free to walk.
- They just let you go?

611
00:46:02.440 --> 00:46:05.273
- They just let me go.
- Just like that?

612
00:46:05.360 --> 00:46:08.034
Just like that.
Come on.

613
00:46:09.400 --> 00:46:12.279
[Millie] If they just let you go,
why are we running?

614
00:46:12.360 --> 00:46:15.113
Well, uh, they really strongly suggested
that we leave town now.

615
00:46:15.200 --> 00:46:18.477
- But what did they say to you?
- Asked me some questions.

616
00:46:18.560 --> 00:46:21.632
- For eight hours?
- They had a lot of questions.

617
00:46:21.720 --> 00:46:24.189
I really want to trust you.
You're making it extremely difficult.

618
00:46:24.280 --> 00:46:26.191
All right. So trust me.
Let's go.

619
00:46:29.520 --> 00:46:31.511
Whoa!

620
00:46:32.760 --> 00:46:34.671
Whoa! Hey.

621
00:46:34.760 --> 00:46:37.593
- Can you take us? Yeah?
<i>- ♪♪ [Car Radio: Rap]</i>

622
00:46:37.680 --> 00:46:40.877
Get in the cab, Millie.
Millie, get in the car.

623
00:46:40.960 --> 00:46:42.871
[Clears Throat]

624
00:46:42.960 --> 00:46:46.032
Please.
Please get in the cab.

625
00:46:46.120 --> 00:46:48.714
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

626
00:46:51.720 --> 00:46:54.314
<i>[Chattering]</i>

627
00:46:54.400 --> 00:46:57.074
<i>[Woman On P.A.
Speaking Italian]</i>

628
00:47:13.600 --> 00:47:15.477
<i>That's yours.</i>

629
00:47:15.600 --> 00:47:18.069
Remember how I told you you didn't
need to tell me everything?

630
00:47:19.400 --> 00:47:21.437
I changed my mind.

631
00:47:26.520 --> 00:47:28.511
What's in the backpack?

632
00:47:52.600 --> 00:47:54.637
Where did you get that?

633
00:48:01.800 --> 00:48:03.916
I don't want to lie to you.

634
00:48:05.800 --> 00:48:09.111
But you don't want to
tell me the truth either.

635
00:48:12.720 --> 00:48:14.916
I can't get on this flight
with you, Millie.

636
00:48:15.000 --> 00:48:18.231
<i>This is as far as we go together.</i>

637
00:48:33.560 --> 00:48:36.439
<i>- [Woman] To Detroit?</i>
- M m-hmm.

638
00:48:43.840 --> 00:48:45.160
<i>[Cell Phone Beeps]</i>

639
00:48:45.320 --> 00:48:46.515
<i>[Roland]
Roland</i>

640
00:48:46.600 --> 00:48:48.591
[Man]
We lost him, sir.

641
00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:51.671
- How many did you send?
- Two men.

642
00:48:51.760 --> 00:48:54.752
- I told you to send everybody.
- Well, she said two would be enough...

643
00:48:54.840 --> 00:48:56.797
but, uh, they missed him.

644
00:48:56.880 --> 00:48:59.599
It's like he knew we were coming.

645
00:48:59.680 --> 00:49:02.479
We're searching the grid now.

646
00:49:02.560 --> 00:49:06.349
Keep me informed.
I'm taking a different tack.

647
00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:19.634
[Ignition Indicator Beeps]

648
00:49:19.720 --> 00:49:21.711
William Rice?

649
00:49:21.800 --> 00:49:23.279
Yeah.

650
00:49:23.360 --> 00:49:25.351
I.R.S.

651
00:49:26.640 --> 00:49:29.996
Could we, uh, go inside and talk?

652
00:49:32.120 --> 00:49:34.953
I don't have to ask.
That's a courtesy.

653
00:49:35.040 --> 00:49:38.317
<i>- [Chattering On TV]</i>
- So, what's this all about?

654
00:49:38.400 --> 00:49:40.550
Your son. David.

655
00:49:42.520 --> 00:49:45.638
Why? Is he in some kind
of trouble or something?

656
00:49:48.040 --> 00:49:51.829
This will go a lot swifter
if you let me ask the questions.

657
00:49:51.920 --> 00:49:54.878
When's the last time
you saw your son?

658
00:49:55.920 --> 00:49:58.389
Eight years ago.

659
00:50:00.920 --> 00:50:02.877
Eight years?

660
00:50:02.960 --> 00:50:04.951
That's right.

661
00:50:07.240 --> 00:50:09.595
What about friends?

662
00:50:09.680 --> 00:50:11.591
Anybody I can talk to?

663
00:50:11.680 --> 00:50:13.876
He didn't have
a whole lot of friends.

664
00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:16.679
I'd like to talk to
David's mother if I could.

665
00:50:16.760 --> 00:50:20.833
Yeah, me too.
If you find her, tell her I said hello.

666
00:50:20.920 --> 00:50:22.877
That her?

667
00:50:22.960 --> 00:50:25.190
Mary Rice. At least that was
her name back then.

668
00:50:29.600 --> 00:50:32.035
When's the last time you saw her?

669
00:50:32.120 --> 00:50:34.555
She split when the kid turned five.

670
00:50:34.640 --> 00:50:36.551
Five. Oh.

671
00:50:36.640 --> 00:50:38.790
<i>Haven't heard a word since.</i>

672
00:50:45.200 --> 00:50:48.352
If I hear anything,
I'll be sure to give you a holler.

673
00:50:50.720 --> 00:50:53.473
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

674
00:50:53.560 --> 00:50:56.598
- No, you won't.
- No. I won't.

675
00:50:59.800 --> 00:51:02.394
Have you seen the special move
you can do on this new thing?

676
00:51:02.480 --> 00:51:07.077
They've added this new control and, like,
you just... If you... Just double-click it. See that?

677
00:51:07.160 --> 00:51:09.071
What do you say?
Whoa.

678
00:51:09.160 --> 00:51:11.549
<i>[Whoosh]</i>

679
00:51:11.640 --> 00:51:13.597
Still alive, are ya?

680
00:51:13.680 --> 00:51:16.832
<i>[TV: Video Game
Machine Gun Fire]</i>

681
00:51:19.400 --> 00:51:22.119
<i>- [Man On TV] I'm hit!
- [Man #2 On TV] He's dead.</i>

682
00:51:22.200 --> 00:51:25.158
- What? That's just great.
- There's more of them?

683
00:51:25.240 --> 00:51:29.313
<i>Hundreds more. I'm tracking 10 right now
What do you care? There's lots more.</i>

684
00:51:29.400 --> 00:51:32.153
- What about the rest?
- What about the rest?

685
00:51:32.240 --> 00:51:34.356
Like I said, I hunt them.

686
00:51:34.440 --> 00:51:36.431
<i>- Start again.</i>
- So who are these guys?

687
00:51:36.520 --> 00:51:38.272
I told you.
They're Paladins.

688
00:51:38.360 --> 00:51:41.910
Yeah, you told me their name.
You didn't tell me what they want.

689
00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:45.516
<i>- [Machine Gun Fire On TV]</i>
- Well, it's pretty simple,
isn't it? They want us dead.

690
00:51:45.600 --> 00:51:48.752
- Didn't you figure that out yet?
- [Chuckles] Yeah. No, I got that much.

691
00:51:48.840 --> 00:51:50.751
- Good. I'm glad.
- Yeah. Thanks.

692
00:51:50.840 --> 00:51:52.751
- Do you mind just, uh...
- Why?

693
00:51:52.840 --> 00:51:54.751
Because we can do
whatever the hell we want.

694
00:51:54.880 --> 00:51:56.791
- Now can you please just...
- I'm hit!

695
00:51:56.880 --> 00:52:00.191
- He's dead.
- Great. Thanks.

696
00:52:00.280 --> 00:52:02.510
You really don't get it, do you?

697
00:52:02.600 --> 00:52:05.638
Paladins have been killing
Jumpers for years.

698
00:52:05.720 --> 00:52:07.677
Way back since medieval times.

699
00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:11.036
They're fanatics.
Religious nut jobs.

700
00:52:11.120 --> 00:52:13.873
Inquisition. Witch hunts.
That was them.

701
00:52:13.960 --> 00:52:17.954
Look. They're smart.
They're fast. They're organized.

702
00:52:18.040 --> 00:52:20.475
No matter what, they'll kill anyone
that gets in their way.

703
00:52:20.560 --> 00:52:24.394
Like your family.
Your friends.

704
00:52:24.480 --> 00:52:28.235
That little girlfriend
you're traipsing around Rome with you.

705
00:52:28.320 --> 00:52:32.553
They're dead.
All of 'em.

706
00:52:32.640 --> 00:52:35.280
Get used to it.
It's just a matter of time.

707
00:52:38.520 --> 00:52:41.160
I'm gonna get some takeaway.
Do you want some?

708
00:52:41.240 --> 00:52:43.151
<i>[Whoosh]</i>

709
00:52:43.240 --> 00:52:45.914
<i>[Airplane Engine Roaring]</i>

710
00:52:50.280 --> 00:52:52.317
<i>[Chattering]</i>

711
00:53:01.600 --> 00:53:03.557
<i>[Chattering On TV]</i>

712
00:53:03.640 --> 00:53:05.631
[Hinges Squeak]

713
00:53:07.680 --> 00:53:09.671
<i>[Chattering Continues]</i>

714
00:53:14.120 --> 00:53:15.758
He's your father.

715
00:53:15.840 --> 00:53:18.958
I'm sorry. I talked to him,
but he wouldn't budge.

716
00:53:19.040 --> 00:53:22.590
<i>He can be so stubborn.
I don't know how my mother puts up with him.</i>

717
00:53:36.800 --> 00:53:38.950
Somebody get some help!

718
00:53:40.680 --> 00:53:42.876
- Now!
<i>- [Man] What happened?</i>

719
00:53:42.960 --> 00:53:45.395
<i>- [Woman] What's going on in here?
- [Chattering]</i>

720
00:53:48.320 --> 00:53:50.072
<i>- [Man] Get the paddles.
- [Shouting]</i>

721
00:53:50.160 --> 00:53:52.117
<i>[Chattering]</i>

722
00:53:54.120 --> 00:53:56.430
You okay? Stay still.

723
00:53:59.000 --> 00:54:00.991
<i>[Man]
I'm not getting a pulse.</i>

724
00:54:03.640 --> 00:54:05.631
<i>What the hell happened here?</i>

725
00:54:08.720 --> 00:54:10.677
Oh!

726
00:54:11.680 --> 00:54:13.432
<i>- [Whoosh]</i>
- Mark.

727
00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:15.995
- Jesus Christ.
- What did you tell him?

728
00:54:16.080 --> 00:54:18.071
- How did they know about Ann Arbor?
- Don't touch me.

729
00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:20.879
- Who'd you tell?
- Stay the hell away from me.

730
00:54:20.960 --> 00:54:23.998
Was it a black guy with white hair?
Was his name Roland?

731
00:54:24.080 --> 00:54:25.991
Just answer the question...

732
00:54:26.080 --> 00:54:28.310
or I'll drop you off the top
of Mount Everest, okay?

733
00:54:28.400 --> 00:54:30.311
- What? What?
- What did you tell him?

734
00:54:30.400 --> 00:54:32.755
I don't... What? Tell what?

735
00:54:32.840 --> 00:54:34.751
I know you told him
about home, all right?

736
00:54:34.840 --> 00:54:37.719
I know you told him about Ann Arbor.
Did you tell him about Millie?

737
00:54:37.800 --> 00:54:39.473
I told him everything.

738
00:54:39.560 --> 00:54:41.836
Why?
Why did you do that?

739
00:54:41.920 --> 00:54:44.230
- Why not?
- [Shouts]

740
00:54:44.320 --> 00:54:46.277
<i>Who are you?</i>

741
00:54:47.400 --> 00:54:49.391
<i>[Wind Howling]</i>

742
00:54:52.960 --> 00:54:55.110
Whoa! Whew!

743
00:54:55.200 --> 00:54:57.111
Where'd the Paladin go?

744
00:54:57.200 --> 00:54:59.669
- Swimming.
- Pacific?

745
00:54:59.760 --> 00:55:03.390
No. Actually, Atlantic.
N ice little shark pit round Cuba.

746
00:55:05.120 --> 00:55:07.396
<i>Uh, what do you think you're doing?</i>

747
00:55:07.480 --> 00:55:09.949
- Put that stuff back!
- Actually, I need to borrow a few things.

748
00:55:10.040 --> 00:55:12.395
Just stay away from the wall!

749
00:55:12.480 --> 00:55:13.959
I'll cut your eyes out.

750
00:55:14.080 --> 00:55:16.469
[Grunts]
I need to find Roland.

751
00:55:16.560 --> 00:55:18.949
No, you don't.
No, you don't.

752
00:55:19.040 --> 00:55:21.111
- I only got eight hours.
- Eight hours?

753
00:55:21.200 --> 00:55:23.157
There's a girl...
Her flight lands in eight hours.

754
00:55:23.240 --> 00:55:25.038
Think that stuff's gonna help?
That stuff's four years old.

755
00:55:25.120 --> 00:55:27.919
<i>Do you want me to jump you back to
high school so you can learn something?</i>

756
00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:30.913
I've been tracking him for 10 years.
Look at this. Look.

757
00:55:33.080 --> 00:55:36.357
You see this?
Our first round in Nepal.

758
00:55:36.440 --> 00:55:38.716
You should see the one he gave me
back in Prague.

759
00:55:38.800 --> 00:55:41.599
Look. Forget it.
Forget Roland.

760
00:55:41.680 --> 00:55:43.671
Don't waste your time.

761
00:55:43.760 --> 00:55:45.831
Just leave it to me.

762
00:55:57.920 --> 00:55:59.877
- Do you mind?
- Look.

763
00:56:00.000 --> 00:56:02.116
Little, uh... Little privacy here?

764
00:56:02.200 --> 00:56:04.589
You know, this is
kind of my thing. Just...

765
00:56:04.680 --> 00:56:08.310
Just... Get... You know, turn around.

766
00:56:08.400 --> 00:56:10.357
Yeah.

767
00:56:10.440 --> 00:56:14.798
I'm... I was thinking
that if we do this together...

768
00:56:14.880 --> 00:56:16.791
we could get him.

769
00:56:16.880 --> 00:56:18.996
What? You mean, like, you and me?

770
00:56:19.080 --> 00:56:21.640
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- Like we team up?

771
00:56:21.720 --> 00:56:24.394
- Yeah.
- [Chuckles]

772
00:56:24.480 --> 00:56:26.994
Look. I'm sorry,
but I don't play well with others.

773
00:56:42.880 --> 00:56:46.396
<i>Do me a favor, yeah?
Don't be here when I get back.</i>

774
00:56:46.480 --> 00:56:49.199
Find a rock. Crawl under it.
Stay there.

775
00:56:57.720 --> 00:57:00.234
<i>Joi woo,</i> brother.

776
00:57:00.320 --> 00:57:02.834
That's "good-bye" in Chinese.

777
00:57:15.840 --> 00:57:17.831
<i>[Chattering]</i>

778
00:57:21.680 --> 00:57:24.672
<i>[People Arguing In Japanese]</i>

779
00:57:29.440 --> 00:57:32.751
Yeah. No. I've been meaning to call.
Really. I still really want to get the tattoo.

780
00:57:32.840 --> 00:57:34.353
[Japanese]

781
00:57:39.040 --> 00:57:41.714
[Horn Honks]

782
00:57:44.720 --> 00:57:46.870
- [Horn Honks]
- [Man Shouts In Japanese]

783
00:57:56.680 --> 00:57:58.671
<i>[Whoosh]</i>

784
00:58:08.520 --> 00:58:10.477
You can't keep following me.

785
00:58:10.560 --> 00:58:13.313
<i>Actually... [Clears Throat]
I'm the one person who can.</i>

786
00:58:13.400 --> 00:58:15.357
Yeah, lucky me.

787
00:58:16.640 --> 00:58:18.790
<i>[Horns Honking]</i>

788
00:58:28.600 --> 00:58:30.910
Why are you walking?

789
00:58:31.000 --> 00:58:34.356
I mean, I... I know Tokyo pretty well.
I got a lot of jump sites here.

790
00:58:34.440 --> 00:58:39.196
You know, I-I... I like walking for a change.
Makes me feel normal.

791
00:58:39.280 --> 00:58:42.432
You, uh... You ever read
Marvel Team-up?

792
00:58:42.520 --> 00:58:44.431
Yeah, I read it. And?

793
00:58:44.520 --> 00:58:49.230
Two superheroes joining forces
for, like, uh, a limited run.

794
00:58:49.320 --> 00:58:52.312
I see what you're trying to do, yeah?
I'm not buying it.

795
00:58:52.400 --> 00:58:55.836
For your own sake, just go home.

796
00:58:55.920 --> 00:58:58.719
- You live in a cave.
- It's called a lair.

797
00:58:58.800 --> 00:59:00.791
And what's the point?

798
00:59:00.880 --> 00:59:04.999
I'm just saying, you know.
We, uh, kind of have this common thing.

799
00:59:07.280 --> 00:59:09.317
And I know where to find Roland.

800
00:59:12.440 --> 00:59:14.477
<i>[Chattering]</i>

801
00:59:20.840 --> 00:59:22.831
[David]
So we doing this, or what?

802
00:59:32.080 --> 00:59:34.071
<i>[Engine Starts]</i>

803
00:59:38.920 --> 00:59:41.719
<i>Whoo!</i>

804
00:59:50.000 --> 00:59:52.071
Sorry. Clutch stuck.

805
00:59:53.880 --> 00:59:56.918
- You're real subtle.
- Yeah, I'm not gonna get rid of you, am I?

806
01:00:00.800 --> 01:00:03.553
[Horns Honking]

807
01:00:13.760 --> 01:00:14.955
Whoa. Whoa.

808
01:00:15.040 --> 01:00:17.350
You might want to hold on, son.

809
01:00:19.040 --> 01:00:20.155
[Screams]

810
01:00:29.400 --> 01:00:32.040
<i>[Horns Honking]</i>

811
01:00:33.800 --> 01:00:35.950
That was close.

812
01:00:36.040 --> 01:00:38.714
Not bad.

813
01:00:38.800 --> 01:00:41.997
This thing must be two tons, easy.
How are you, uh...

814
01:00:42.080 --> 01:00:44.435
If it moves, I can jump it.

815
01:00:44.520 --> 01:00:47.797
<i>Actually, I knew this Jumper once...
crazy bastard...</i>

816
01:00:47.880 --> 01:00:50.190
tried to hop a whole building.
[Chuckles]

817
01:00:50.280 --> 01:00:52.715
- Won't be trying that again.
- Why's that?

818
01:00:52.800 --> 01:00:55.314
That's 'cause he's dead.
Killed him.

819
01:00:55.400 --> 01:00:59.030
Still managed to shake it
a little though.

820
01:01:02.720 --> 01:01:05.109
<i>So how long you been doing this for?</i>

821
01:01:05.200 --> 01:01:07.874
- Doing what? Driving?
- No. Jumping.

822
01:01:07.960 --> 01:01:09.917
<i>- [Radio Channels Changing]</i>
- Since I was five.

823
01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:11.911
- Five?
- Yeah.

824
01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:15.436
<i>- ♪♪ [Radio: Rock]</i>
- How'd you keep it a secret from people?

825
01:01:15.520 --> 01:01:18.876
<i>- Like your parents.</i>
- It's pretty easy when they're not around.

826
01:01:18.960 --> 01:01:21.270
<i>- ♪♪ [Radio: Heavy Metal]</i>
- Where were they?

827
01:01:21.360 --> 01:01:23.351
Not around.

828
01:01:27.720 --> 01:01:30.758
You know, my mom...
she took off when I was five.

829
01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:34.550
<i>I know what it's like
to not, you know...</i>

830
01:01:34.640 --> 01:01:37.109
My dad, he...

831
01:01:37.200 --> 01:01:39.589
Did I ask about your family?

832
01:01:40.800 --> 01:01:43.838
I mean, are we on
<i>Oprah</i> here or...

833
01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:49.998
<i>- ♪♪ [Heavy Metal]
- ♪ Do you want it
Do you need it</i> ♪

834
01:01:50.080 --> 01:01:52.594
♪ <i>Let me hear it
Ladies and gentlemen♪♪</i>

835
01:01:52.680 --> 01:01:55.513
<i>[David]
Griffin, I can't keep doing this. I gotta go.</i>

836
01:01:55.600 --> 01:01:58.399
Her flight lands any second.
I need an answer.

837
01:01:59.680 --> 01:02:01.353
- [Horn Honks]
- [Man Shouts]

838
01:02:01.440 --> 01:02:05.559
This is it, all right?
Marvel Team-up, now or never.

839
01:02:05.640 --> 01:02:09.315
- [Horn Honks]
- A very limited run, right?

840
01:02:09.400 --> 01:02:12.392
Save her, kill him, you know.
We're done.

841
01:02:12.480 --> 01:02:14.994
All right, Spidey.

842
01:02:16.840 --> 01:02:18.797
Hey!

843
01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:21.071
<i>[Man On PA.]
Due to increased security measures, all bags...</i>

844
01:02:21.160 --> 01:02:24.391
- Hey!
<i>- Detroit International Airport asks you...</i>

845
01:02:24.480 --> 01:02:26.517
<i>to keep your bags in your
possession at all times.</i>

846
01:02:26.600 --> 01:02:31.037
<i>[Woman On P.A.] Flight 427 to Cleveland
will now be boarding at Gate Number5.</i>

847
01:02:32.320 --> 01:02:36.109
- Hey.
- The flight from Rome landed an hour ago.

848
01:02:36.200 --> 01:02:38.191
Oh, no.

849
01:02:39.200 --> 01:02:42.989
<i>You didn't check on the flight?</i>

850
01:02:43.080 --> 01:02:45.469
All right. Well, we gotta find her,
you know.

851
01:02:45.560 --> 01:02:48.598
You go find her. I'm gonna arm up.
Meet me back at the lair.

852
01:02:48.680 --> 01:02:50.591
- All right?
- Fine.

853
01:02:50.680 --> 01:02:51.670
[Gasps]

854
01:02:51.760 --> 01:02:54.115
<i>[Woman On PA., Indistinct]</i>

855
01:02:54.200 --> 01:02:56.157
What you looking at?

856
01:03:00.120 --> 01:03:02.031
Boo!

857
01:03:06.120 --> 01:03:11.035
Hey. U h, I'm Millie's friend,
David. Is she here?

858
01:03:11.120 --> 01:03:12.872
Last I checked she was with you.

859
01:03:14.200 --> 01:03:16.510
Hey. Your friend came by.

860
01:03:18.200 --> 01:03:21.955
- What are you talking about?
- Black guy, white hair. You just missed him.

861
01:03:40.080 --> 01:03:41.912
[Beeping]

862
01:03:43.000 --> 01:03:44.991
[Line Ringing]

863
01:03:48.920 --> 01:03:51.560
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

864
01:03:51.680 --> 01:03:53.671
<i>[Ringing Continues]</i>

865
01:03:54.800 --> 01:03:56.711
[Gasps]

866
01:03:56.800 --> 01:03:59.474
- Jesus.
- Hey.

867
01:03:59.560 --> 01:04:01.471
<i>David, wh...</i>

868
01:04:02.560 --> 01:04:04.597
What the hell are you doing here?

869
01:04:04.680 --> 01:04:06.910
I buzzed, but you didn't pick up.

870
01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:10.834
- So you just broke in?
- Yeah. Well, I needed to
make sure that you were okay.

871
01:04:10.920 --> 01:04:14.515
<i>No, David I'm not okay.
I got left in an airport in Rome.</i>

872
01:04:14.600 --> 01:04:17.114
[Exhales Deeply]

873
01:04:17.200 --> 01:04:19.191
I'm sorry.

874
01:04:21.600 --> 01:04:23.511
You're sorry.

875
01:04:23.600 --> 01:04:25.557
Thank you.

876
01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:30.991
I think you should leave.

877
01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:38.193
<i>[Car Doors Opening, Closing]</i>

878
01:04:38.280 --> 01:04:40.191
<i>David, you need to leave!</i>

879
01:04:40.280 --> 01:04:43.193
<i>[Roland] Come on. Snap to it.
We don't have much time.</i>

880
01:04:43.280 --> 01:04:45.556
- What? What are you doing?
- U h...

881
01:04:45.640 --> 01:04:48.553
- David, I told you to leave.
- Uh...

882
01:04:48.640 --> 01:04:51.029
<i>- Um...</i>
- "Um" what?

883
01:04:51.120 --> 01:04:55.398
- I'm not in banking, okay?
- No, really?

884
01:04:55.480 --> 01:04:58.120
- I mean, the money did come
from a bank, you know.
- Yeah.

885
01:04:58.200 --> 01:05:03.149
- U h, a few banks, actually.
- Are... Are you telling me you're a bank robber?

886
01:05:03.240 --> 01:05:05.231
Small part. Uh...

887
01:05:06.880 --> 01:05:09.554
Will you please get out of my house?

888
01:05:10.840 --> 01:05:12.831
[Gasps]

889
01:05:18.240 --> 01:05:19.674
Uh-huh.

890
01:05:20.840 --> 01:05:23.116
- [Screams]
- Millie, I'm sorry.

891
01:05:23.200 --> 01:05:25.669
Wh... Oh, my God. Okay.

892
01:05:25.760 --> 01:05:28.229
<i>- I'm really sorry, but we gotta go.</i>
- Just go. Leave me alone.

893
01:05:28.360 --> 01:05:30.636
Come on.

894
01:05:30.720 --> 01:05:32.438
This might hurt a little bit, okay?

895
01:05:32.520 --> 01:05:35.990
- [Grunts]
- [Screams]

896
01:05:36.080 --> 01:05:38.799
- It's okay.
- Where am I?

897
01:05:38.880 --> 01:05:41.633
Trust me, okay?
[Echoing]

898
01:05:41.720 --> 01:05:43.950
- I'm not gonna hurt you.
- Don't you even come near me.

899
01:05:44.040 --> 01:05:46.111
- Millie.
- Don't even come near me.

900
01:05:49.760 --> 01:05:52.320
I'm gonna explain this, all right?
I'm gonna explain everything.

901
01:05:55.440 --> 01:05:57.431
In here.

902
01:05:57.520 --> 01:06:00.433
Just, uh... Just stay where you are, all right?
Just stay right there.

903
01:06:00.520 --> 01:06:03.194
- David?
- [Roland] Hurry up. It's closing.

904
01:06:16.320 --> 01:06:18.231
[Groans]

905
01:06:23.320 --> 01:06:25.994
<i>Griffin.</i>

906
01:06:26.080 --> 01:06:28.151
There's something I gotta tell ya.

907
01:06:28.240 --> 01:06:30.516
- Did you find her?
- There's something that's gonna piss you off.

908
01:06:30.600 --> 01:06:33.069
- Piss me off?
- David.

909
01:06:33.160 --> 01:06:35.231
What is this?

910
01:06:35.320 --> 01:06:37.072
- David?
- What's she doing here?

911
01:06:37.160 --> 01:06:39.674
- This isn't some kind of clubhouse, you know.
<i>- What is going on?</i>

912
01:06:39.760 --> 01:06:41.353
<i>- Stay inside.</i>
- Wanna see the top of Everest?

913
01:06:41.440 --> 01:06:43.590
- I was trying to tell you.
- Maybe the bottom?

914
01:06:43.680 --> 01:06:45.751
- What?
- Griffin, listen to me. I...

915
01:06:45.840 --> 01:06:47.751
That's what I was
trying to tell you.

916
01:06:47.840 --> 01:06:50.150
By bringing her down here, they can
follow you. They have a machine.

917
01:06:50.240 --> 01:06:52.993
- It can open wormholes and keep them open.
- What are you talking about?

918
01:06:53.080 --> 01:06:54.673
I'm saying they can
follow us anywhere.

919
01:06:54.760 --> 01:06:56.831
And you brought her here.

920
01:06:59.600 --> 01:07:01.591
<i>[Distorted Voices Echoing]</i>

921
01:07:11.040 --> 01:07:13.270
- Shit.
- There's two of you?

922
01:07:13.360 --> 01:07:15.271
David, what is going on?

923
01:07:15.360 --> 01:07:17.874
[Panting]
Millie... Millie, stay right here.

924
01:07:17.960 --> 01:07:19.917
No. No!

925
01:07:21.360 --> 01:07:23.271
- What have you done?
- Griffin...

926
01:07:23.360 --> 01:07:25.351
- Where does this thing go?
- We gotta go.

927
01:07:25.440 --> 01:07:27.272
David, what did you do?

928
01:07:28.480 --> 01:07:29.914
[Groans]

929
01:07:36.840 --> 01:07:39.753
<i>[TV: Video Game
Voices Chattering]</i>

930
01:08:08.960 --> 01:08:10.951
Holy shit.

931
01:08:28.400 --> 01:08:31.040
[Panting]

932
01:08:32.720 --> 01:08:35.473
<i>[Panting]
Mom?</i>

933
01:08:42.200 --> 01:08:45.477
- [Groans]
- [Electricity Crackling]

934
01:08:45.560 --> 01:08:49.190
<i>[Roland]
Thanks for leading me to your friend.</i>

935
01:08:49.280 --> 01:08:53.160
<i>Wait, wait, wait, wait. Why are you
doing this to me? I never hurt you.</i>

936
01:08:53.240 --> 01:08:55.197
I never hurt anybody.

937
01:08:56.400 --> 01:08:58.391
Not yet, but you will.

938
01:08:58.480 --> 01:08:59.993
